## Data Analysis

### Example 2.1: Sales Data Analysis

```typescript
const salesCSV = `date,product,quantity,unitPrice,region
2024-01-15,ProductA,100,25.50,North
2024-01-15,ProductB,50,15.00,South
2024-01-16,ProductA,75,25.50,East
2024-01-16,ProductC,200,8.50,West
2024-01-17,ProductA,120,25.50,North
2024-01-17,ProductB,80,15.00,East`;

const result = parseCSV(salesCSV);

// Calculate total revenue per product
const byProduct = result.groupBy("product");

for (const [product, sales] of byProduct) {
  const revenue = sales.reduce((sum, s) => 
    sum + (s.quantity * s.unitPrice), 0
  );
  console.log(`${product}: $${revenue.toFixed(2)}`);
}
// ProductA: $9382.50
// ProductB: $2200.00
// ProductC: $1700.00

// Find top performing region
const byRegion = result.groupBy("region");
let topRegion = { name: "", total: 0 };

for (const [region, sales] of byRegion) {
  const total = sales.reduce((sum, s) => 
    sum + (s.quantity * s.unitPrice), 0
  );
  if (total > topRegion.total) {
    topRegion = { name: region, total };
  }
}

console.log(`Top region: ${topRegion.name} ($${topRegion.total.toFixed(2)})`);
// Top region: North ($5890.00)
```

### Example 2.2: Student Grades Analysis

```typescript
const gradesCSV = `student,math,science,english,history
